      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "startup-service-dict-drift",
      "summary": "Background service dispatch is defined by duplicated tables (spec list plus switch) with no compile-time link, creating drift risk when service set changes.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go",
        "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator_test.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`startBackgroundServiceSpecs` lists service names such as `startBackgroundServiceVersion`, `startBackgroundServiceDocker`, and others, while `startBackgroundServiceName` values are mapped to callbacks in a separate `startServiceFn` switch.",
        "The switch includes a `default: return nil`, and no static check ensures every spec/constant in the slice has a corresponding callback branch.",
        "The same file has tests that manually recreate callback wiring via `withStartBackgroundServiceCallback` switch-style mapping, increasing the risk of mismatched update behavior across paths."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Replace the spec slice and switch with a single data-driven registry map keyed by `startupBackgroundServiceName` (or a generated table) that contains both metadata and the callback resolver; validate at startup with an explicit completeness check and fail-fast when unknown/duplicate/missing service mappings are detected.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit",
      "root_cause_cluster": "runtime-orchestration-fragile-control-plane"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "startup-logstream-global-seam",
      "summary": "Background service startup runtime resolution pulls `logstreamRuntime` from global session state even when a caller supplies an explicit runtime, reducing substitution boundaries.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go",
        "goseg/system/wifi_runtime_api.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`buildBackgroundServices` uses `resolveStartBackgroundServicesRuntime(logstreamRuntimeFromContext(), ...)` for both concrete and pointer runtime variants, ignoring any higher-level runtime context passed by the caller.",
        "`logstreamRuntimeFromContext()` reads `session.LogstreamRuntimeState()`, calls `logger.ConfigureLogstreamRuntime(systemRuntime)`, and returns a runtime built from that shared state.",
        "`defaultStartBackgroundServicesRuntime` then captures that parameter in closures for `StartSysLogStreamerFn`, `StartDockerLogStreamerFn`, and `StartDockerLogConnRemoverFn`, so these service callbacks are anchored to ambient process state."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Inject logstream runtime explicitly through the startup options/runtime struct and remove `logstreamRuntimeFromContext` from `buildBackgroundServices`; keep `logstreamRuntimeFromContext` only in top-level bootstrap composition with a one-way defaulting path.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "runtime-orchestration-fragile-control-plane"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "broadcast-state-facade-leak",
      "summary": "Broadcast loop introduces a runtime seam for callbacks but still binds to the singleton broadcast state directly in hot paths, weakening the abstraction boundary.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/broadcast/loop.go",
        "goseg/broadcast/state.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`runBroadcastTickWithRuntime` uses `DefaultBroadcastStateRuntime().GetState()` when reading baseline state instead of the supplied runtime seam.",
        "Fallback on failure also uses `DefaultBroadcastStateRuntime().GetState().Urbits`, and new state assignment uses `rt.updateBroadcastFn` where the default runtime closure is itself hardwired to `DefaultBroadcastStateRuntime().UpdateBroadcast(newState)`.",
        "These direct singleton accesses appear alongside the injected seam fields in `broadcastLoopRuntime`, creating a split-brain abstraction where some behavior is seam-driven and core state access is hardcoded."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Make the loop runtime own and use a `stateRuntime` field consistently for all state reads/writes in `runBroadcastTickWithRuntime` (including error fallback), and pass that runtime in tests; this keeps the loop fully injectable and removes hidden singleton coupling.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "runtime-orchestration-fragile-control-plane"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Service orchestration control logic is spread across parallel registries and ambient globals instead of a single coherent boundary representation.",
      "Defaulting paths mix construction-time defaults, runtime composition, and execution-time global lookups, making seam usage inconsistent.",
